              "id": "CVE-2025-48924",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Uncontrolled Recursion vulnerability in Apache Commons Lang.  This iss ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Uncontrolled Recursion vulnerability in Apache Commons Lang.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons Lang: Starting with commons-lang:commons-lang 2.0 to 2.6, and, from org.apache.commons:commons-lang3 3.0 before 3.18.0.\n\nThe methods ClassUtils.getClass(...) can throw StackOverflowError on very long inputs. Because an Error is usually not handled by applications and libraries, a \nStackOverflowError could cause an application to stop.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 3.18.0, which fixes the issue."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48924",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-48924\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: commons-lang:commons-lang\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2025-48924](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48924)\nUncontrolled Recursion vulnerability in Apache Commons Lang.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons Lang: Starting with commons-lang:commons-lang 2.0 to 2.6, and, from org.apache.commons:commons-lang3 3.0 before 3.18.0.\n\nThe methods ClassUtils.getClass(...) can throw StackOverflowError on very long inputs. Because an Error is usually not handled by applications and libraries, a \nStackOverflowError could cause an application to stop.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 3.18.0, which fixes the issue.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-48924**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|commons-lang:commons-lang||[CVE-2025-48924](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48924)|\n\nUncontrolled Recursion vulnerability in Apache Commons Lang.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons Lang: Starting with commons-lang:commons-lang 2.0 to 2.6, and, from org.apache.commons:commons-lang3 3.0 before 3.18.0.\n\nThe methods ClassUtils.getClass(...) can throw StackOverflowError on very long inputs. Because an Error is usually not handled by applications and libraries, a \nStackOverflowError could cause an application to stop.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 3.18.0, which fixes the issue."
