            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-42795",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "tomcat: improper cleaning of recycled objects could lead to information leak"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Incomplete Cleanup vulnerability in Apache Tomcat.When recycling various internal objects in Apache Tomcat from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.0-M11, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.13, from 9.0.0-M1 through 9.0.80 and from 8.5.0 through 8.5.93, an error could \ncause Tomcat to skip some parts of the recycling process leading to \ninformation leaking from the current request/response to the next.\nOlder, EOL versions may also be affected.\n\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.0-M12 onwards, 10.1.14 onwards, 9.0.81 onwards or 8.5.94 onwards, which fixes the issue."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-42795",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2023-42795\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core\nFixed Version: 11.0.0-M12, 10.1.14, 9.0.81, 8.5.94\nLink: [CVE-2023-42795](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-42795)\nIncomplete Cleanup vulnerability in Apache Tomcat.When recycling various internal objects in Apache Tomcat from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.0-M11, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.13, from 9.0.0-M1 through 9.0.80 and from 8.5.0 through 8.5.93, an error could \ncause Tomcat to skip some parts of the recycling process leading to \ninformation leaking from the current request/response to the next.\nOlder, EOL versions may also be affected.\n\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.0-M12 onwards, 10.1.14 onwards, 9.0.81 onwards or 8.5.94 onwards, which fixes the issue.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2023-42795**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core|11.0.0-M12, 10.1.14, 9.0.81, 8.5.94|[CVE-2023-42795](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-42795)|\n\nIncomplete Cleanup vulnerability in Apache Tomcat.When recycling various internal objects in Apache Tomcat from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.0-M11, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.13, from 9.0.0-M1 through 9.0.80 and from 8.5.0 through 8.5.93, an error could \ncause Tomcat to skip some parts of the recycling process leading to \ninformation leaking from the current request/response to the next.\nOlder, EOL versions may also be affected.\n\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.0-M12 onwards, 10.1.14 onwards, 9.0.81 onwards or 8.5.94 onwards, which fixes the issue."
              },
