            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-25854",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Apache Tomcat: Apache Tomcat: Open Redirect vulnerability via LoadBalancerDrainingValve"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Occasional URL redirection to untrusted Site ('Open Redirect') vulnerability in Apache Tomcat via the LoadBalancerDrainingValve.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat: from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.18, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.52, from 9.0.0.M23 through 9.0.115, from 8.5.30 through 8.5.100.\nOther, unsupported versions may also be affected\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.20, 10.1.53 or 9.0.116, which fix the issue."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-25854",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-25854\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core\nFixed Version: 9.0.116, 10.1.53, 11.0.20\nLink: [CVE-2026-25854](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-25854)\nOccasional URL redirection to untrusted Site ('Open Redirect') vulnerability in Apache Tomcat via the LoadBalancerDrainingValve.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Tomcat: from 11.0.0-M1 through 11.0.18, from 10.1.0-M1 through 10.1.52, from 9.0.0.M23 through 9.0.115, from 8.5.30 through 8.5.100.\nOther, unsupported versions may also be affected\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 11.0.20, 10.1.53 or 9.0.116, which fix the issue.",
