            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-20860",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "springframework: Security Bypass With Un-Prefixed Double Wildcard Pattern"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Spring Framework running version 6.0.0 - 6.0.6 or 5.3.0 - 5.3.25 using \"**\" as a pattern in Spring Security configuration with the mvcRequestMatcher creates a mismatch in pattern matching between Spring Security and Spring MVC, and the potential for a security bypass."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-20860",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2023-20860\nSeverity: CRITICAL\nPackage: org.springframework:spring-webmvc\nFixed Version: 6.0.7, 5.3.26\nLink: [CVE-2023-20860](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-20860)\nSpring Framework running version 6.0.0 - 6.0.6 or 5.3.0 - 5.3.25 using \"**\" as a pattern in Spring Security configuration with the mvcRequestMatcher creates a mismatch in pattern matching between Spring Security and Spring MVC, and the potential for a security bypass.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2023-20860**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|CRITICAL|org.springframework:spring-webmvc|6.0.7, 5.3.26|[CVE-2023-20860](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2023-20860)|\n\nSpring Framework running version 6.0.0 - 6.0.6 or 5.3.0 - 5.3.25 using \"**\" as a pattern in Spring Security configuration with the mvcRequestMatcher creates a mismatch in pattern matching between Spring Security and Spring MVC, and the potential for a security bypass."
              },
