            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-22745",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "spring-webflux: Spring MVC and Spring WebFlux: Denial of Service via slow static resource resolution on Windows"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Spring MVC and WebFlux applications are vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks when resolving static resources.\n\n\nMore precisely, an application can be vulnerable when all the following are true:\n\n  *  the application is using Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux\n  *  the application is serving static resources from the file system\n  *  the application is running on a Windows platform\n\n\nWhen all the conditions above are met, the attacker can send malicious requests that are slow to resolve and that can keep HTTP connections in use. This can cause a Denial of Service on the application."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22745",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-22745\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: org.springframework:spring-webmvc\nFixed Version: 7.0.7, 6.2.18\nLink: [CVE-2026-22745](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22745)\nSpring MVC and WebFlux applications are vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks when resolving static resources.\n\n\nMore precisely, an application can be vulnerable when all the following are true:\n\n  *  the application is using Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux\n  *  the application is serving static resources from the file system\n  *  the application is running on a Windows platform\n\n\nWhen all the conditions above are met, the attacker can send malicious requests that are slow to resolve and that can keep HTTP connections in use. This can cause a Denial of Service on the application.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-22745**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|org.springframework:spring-webmvc|7.0.7, 6.2.18|[CVE-2026-22745](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22745)|\n\nSpring MVC and WebFlux applications are vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks when resolving static resources.\n\n\nMore precisely, an application can be vulnerable when all the following are true:\n\n  *  the application is using Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux\n  *  the application is serving static resources from the file system\n  *  the application is running on a Windows platform\n\n\nWhen all the conditions above are met, the attacker can send malicious requests that are slow to resolve and that can keep HTTP connections in use. This can cause a Denial of Service on the application."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.3,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L",
